00:11:39.600 --> 00:11:41.750
to can... I had a lady named Sherry.

00:11:41.760 --> 00:11:44.069
She was into canning food. She

00:11:44.079 --> 00:11:46.310
learned how to can

00:11:46.320 --> 00:11:48.069
pot roast meals and

00:11:48.079 --> 00:11:50.150
stored her house full of

00:11:50.160 --> 00:11:52.470
that, which was pretty brilliant

00:11:52.470 --> 00:11:52.480
because

00:11:52.480 --> 00:11:54.389
she eats that. She's a

00:11:54.399 --> 00:11:59.030
friend of ours from the old church.

00:11:59.040 --> 00:12:01.750
You get ideas that God will

00:12:01.760 --> 00:12:04.310
give you to sustain things, and you can

00:12:04.320 --> 00:12:06.230
eat it and rotate it out so you

00:12:06.240 --> 00:12:09.430
always have extra. Then

00:12:09.430 --> 00:12:09.440
there

00:12:09.440 --> 00:12:14.230
are

00:12:14.240 --> 00:12:18.150
Tower Gardens. Now, Tower Gardens are

00:12:18.160 --> 00:12:20.550
very wise. We

00:12:20.560 --> 00:12:23.110
have two of them, and you can grow your

00:12:23.120 --> 00:12:25.350
vegetables

00:12:25.360 --> 00:12:28.069
from these Tower Gardens that

00:12:28.079 --> 00:12:30.310
have lights on them. You

00:12:30.320 --> 00:12:32.710
can have a backup in case the grid

00:12:32.720 --> 00:12:35.350
goes down that runs off solar

00:12:35.350 --> 00:12:35.360
power.

00:12:35.360 --> 00:12:38.470
Solar power runs outside your

00:12:38.480 --> 00:12:40.310
house a little bit during the day

00:12:40.310 --> 00:12:40.320
so

00:12:40.320 --> 00:12:43.750
these lights shine during the winter.

00:12:46.079 --> 00:12:47.590
They have

00:12:47.600 --> 00:12:49.829
little seed pods, and

00:12:49.839 --> 00:12:51.590
you can grow tomatoes,

00:12:51.600 --> 00:12:53.030
cucumbers,

00:12:53.040 --> 00:12:55.590
lettuce, cabbage,

00:12:57.279 --> 00:12:59.990
carrots, whatever. It

00:13:00.000 --> 00:13:01.750
grows out of this and

00:13:01.760 --> 00:13:04.150
has a base where the water is always

00:13:04.160 --> 00:13:07.269
filtering up through it and feeds

00:13:07.279 --> 00:13:11.190
the plants what they need to sustain

00:13:11.200 --> 00:13:13.590
life. If you do it right, it'll

00:13:13.600 --> 00:13:17.590
produce five pounds of food a week

00:13:17.600 --> 00:13:20.949
per garden.

00:13:20.959 --> 00:13:23.269
You go by how much your family may

00:13:23.279 --> 00:13:25.910
need. Some say, 'Our family

00:13:25.920 --> 00:13:29.110
would eat 20 pounds of

00:13:29.120 --> 00:13:31.350
vegetables a week,'which is a lot.

00:13:31.360 --> 00:13:33.110
Ten

00:13:33.120 --> 00:13:36.710
for us. That's if

00:13:36.720 --> 00:13:38.550
you're just eating a vegan diet. You

00:13:38.560 --> 00:13:40.150
can eat a lot of vegan with

00:13:40.160 --> 00:13:43.269
some bread and good grains and

00:13:43.279 --> 00:13:44.949
sustain your life.

00:13:46.000 --> 00:13:49.030
We're not vegan, but

00:13:49.040 --> 00:13:53.110
meat takes cold to stay fresh.

00:13:53.120 --> 00:13:55.030
It's hard to keep meat fresh if the

00:13:55.040 --> 00:13:57.430
grid's down. I have seen

00:13:57.430 --> 00:13:57.440
things

00:13:57.440 --> 00:14:00.310
about cyberattacks and electricity

00:14:00.320 --> 00:14:02.230
attacks where people are without this stuff for three and four

00:14:02.240 --> 00:14:04.949
weeks at a time.

00:14:04.959 --> 00:14:06.710
We're praying

00:14:06.720 --> 00:14:08.949
against it, but if it were to

00:14:08.959 --> 00:14:11.030
happen, how could you sustain your

00:14:11.040 --> 00:14:12.790
hamburger?

00:14:12.800 --> 00:14:14.710
How would you keep your freezer going?

00:14:14.720 --> 00:14:16.550
I have a generator. How long

00:14:16.560 --> 00:14:19.110
can you keep a generator going with gas

00:14:19.110 --> 00:14:19.120
or

00:14:19.120 --> 00:14:22.310
natural gas for

00:14:22.320 --> 00:14:24.069
a long period? You could run it

00:14:24.079 --> 00:14:26.069
every three hours,

00:14:26.079 --> 00:14:30.470
but what if it's longer? I don't like

00:14:30.480 --> 00:14:32.629
to get into this

00:14:32.639 --> 00:14:34.470
because it becomes controversial for a lot

00:14:34.480 --> 00:14:35.990
of people, but I felt in my

00:14:36.000 --> 00:14:38.150
heart to do it tonight, and you can take

00:14:38.160 --> 00:14:40.870
it for what you want. Having a Tower

00:14:40.880 --> 00:14:43.509
Garden running off solar and a battery

00:14:44.560 --> 00:14:46.230
generator... it's a little thing; it's a

00:14:46.240 --> 00:14:48.870
Jackery.

00:14:48.880 --> 00:14:50.069
They have all different kinds of

00:14:50.079 --> 00:14:51.269
brands, but it's one of those

00:14:51.279 --> 00:14:52.790
little ones.

00:14:55.600 --> 00:14:57.350
I think we do have

00:14:57.360 --> 00:14:57.990
a

00:14:58.949 --> 00:14:58.959
Jackery.

00:14:59.199 --> 00:15:01.430
It

00:15:01.440 --> 00:15:02.949
lasts hours,

00:15:02.959 --> 00:15:04.629
and you can run a microwave on it for

00:15:04.639 --> 00:15:06.389
four or five hours. I think

00:15:06.399 --> 00:15:08.790
we paid like 800 bucks for it,

00:15:08.800 --> 00:15:11.269
and you can

00:15:11.279 --> 00:15:13.829
run your Tower Garden off of it and keep

00:15:13.839 --> 00:15:15.269
your plants alive.

00:15:26.560 --> 00:15:28.470
I'm not

00:15:28.480 --> 00:15:29.990
telling you what you should do; I'm

00:15:30.000 --> 00:15:31.750
trying to tell you what we do

00:15:31.760 --> 00:15:33.189
because we eat it anyway.

00:15:33.199 --> 00:15:35.430
It's not

00:15:35.440 --> 00:15:36.310
fear.

00:15:36.320 --> 00:15:38.629
It's good to eat vegetables

00:15:38.629 --> 00:15:38.639
and

00:15:38.639 --> 00:15:42.790
fresh bread.

00:15:45.920 --> 00:15:48.550
This is

00:15:48.550 --> 00:15:48.560
sustainable.

00:15:48.560 --> 00:15:51.509
You can buy tubs of it,

00:15:51.509 --> 00:15:51.519
rotate

00:15:51.519 --> 00:15:53.430
it out,

00:15:53.440 --> 00:15:55.189
and I don't know how many

00:16:06.959 --> 00:16:08.710
loaves of bread you can make with this

00:16:08.720 --> 00:16:09.590
and muffins.

00:16:09.600 --> 00:16:11.590
This turns

00:16:11.600 --> 00:16:14.389
into a lot.

00:16:16.480 --> 00:16:17.829
It expands when you mill it.

00:16:18.800 --> 00:16:19.990
It's fluffier.

00:16:19.990 --> 00:16:20.000
It

00:16:20.000 --> 00:16:21.749
looks like very little,

00:16:21.759 --> 00:16:23.189
but when you

00:16:23.199 --> 00:16:24.710
grind it up, it turns into a lot.

00:16:24.720 --> 00:16:27.590
If that was already milled, it would be

00:16:27.600 --> 00:16:29.509
a lot

00:16:30.560 --> 00:16:31.670
bigger.

00:16:33.680 --> 00:16:36.629
This right here is for backup,

00:16:36.639 --> 00:16:37.829
for power.

00:16:37.839 --> 00:16:39.269
We're not selling the brand.

00:16:39.279 --> 00:16:41.590
I'm not

00:16:41.600 --> 00:16:43.430
trying to sponsor it; I'm just trying to

00:16:43.440 --> 00:16:44.790
tell you.

00:16:44.800 --> 00:16:46.470
There

00:16:48.230 --> 00:16:48.240
are

00:16:49.120 --> 00:16:51.110
a lot of different brands that

00:16:51.120 --> 00:16:54.069
are amazing, but this is the one we got,

00:16:54.079 --> 00:16:56.310
and we plug our stuff into it. We

00:16:56.320 --> 00:16:57.670
got it on sale

00:16:58.880 --> 00:17:00.629
off

00:17:00.639 --> 00:17:01.189
Amazon,

00:17:01.189 --> 00:17:01.199
maybe

00:17:01.199 --> 00:17:02.629
Black Friday, so they

00:17:02.639 --> 00:17:03.829
might have good deals going on right

00:17:03.839 --> 00:17:04.150
now.

00:17:04.160 --> 00:17:06.949
We got solar

00:17:06.959 --> 00:17:08.710
panels and it charges it.

00:17:08.720 --> 00:17:10.549
In case of emergency, you put the

00:17:10.559 --> 00:17:12.230
solar panel out and it keeps stuff

00:17:12.240 --> 00:17:13.829
going.

00:17:13.839 --> 00:17:15.350
I'm just trying to give alternative

00:17:15.360 --> 00:17:19.270
ideas for you. I don't like the

00:17:19.270 --> 00:17:19.280
30-year

00:17:19.280 --> 00:17:20.870
shelf life food.

00:17:20.880 --> 00:17:22.390
I don't think it's healthy for the body

00:17:22.400 --> 00:17:23.590
of Christ.

00:17:23.600 --> 00:17:25.350
If you believe in

00:17:25.360 --> 00:17:26.949
it and you sell it, that's on

00:17:26.959 --> 00:17:28.870
you. I'm just trying to say: what are

00:17:28.880 --> 00:17:31.750
alternative ideas that could help

00:17:31.760 --> 00:17:32.470
you,

00:17:32.470 --> 00:17:32.480
things

00:17:32.480 --> 00:17:34.230
you're already consuming

00:17:34.230 --> 00:17:34.240
that

00:17:34.240 --> 00:17:34.950
aren't

00:17:34.960 --> 00:17:37.029
way out there?

00:17:37.039 --> 00:17:40.150
The next thing would be chickens. Now, I

00:17:40.160 --> 00:17:43.990
know Sister Billie and her

00:17:44.000 --> 00:17:45.990
ministry; they have 30 chickens or

00:17:46.000 --> 00:17:47.270
more. I mean, they have a lot of

00:17:47.280 --> 00:17:50.390
chickens. Her son Terry and the

00:17:50.390 --> 00:17:50.400
rest of

00:17:50.400 --> 00:17:52.310
them have chickens; they lay

00:17:52.320 --> 00:17:54.470
eggs out there, and they fish

00:17:54.470 --> 00:17:54.480
and

00:17:54.480 --> 00:17:56.950
hunt. But we

00:17:56.960 --> 00:18:00.390
live in the city, so you can't

00:18:00.400 --> 00:18:03.110
kill deer, hunt, and fish

00:18:03.120 --> 00:18:04.230
because we don't have

00:18:04.240 --> 00:18:06.549
a place to go. So, you have to

00:18:06.559 --> 00:18:08.549
think outside the box. If you live in a

00:18:08.559 --> 00:18:11.830
major city like Chicago or New York,

00:18:11.840 --> 00:18:13.830
what could you

00:18:13.840 --> 00:18:17.990
do in case of an emergency?

00:18:18.000 --> 00:18:20.150
I bring all this up for a reason, but I

00:18:20.160 --> 00:18:22.789
just don't get into it.

00:18:22.799 --> 00:18:24.710
There's much you do not know that I do

00:18:24.720 --> 00:18:27.590
not say, but that I pray over. I'm telling

00:18:27.600 --> 00:18:30.070
you now, there was a group of us in

00:18:30.080 --> 00:18:34.070
2015 in our old church. We got

00:18:34.080 --> 00:18:36.390
all into survivalism, and

00:18:36.400 --> 00:18:38.870
people got into saving things

00:18:38.880 --> 00:18:40.789
back. People get

00:18:40.799 --> 00:18:43.750
real flaky with it.

00:18:43.760 --> 00:18:46.070
I never try to give advice, but I

00:18:46.080 --> 00:18:47.590
see these things and we pray

00:18:47.590 --> 00:18:47.600
over them.

00:18:47.600 --> 00:18:49.590
I had one YouTuber say,

00:18:49.600 --> 00:18:51.190
'You're saying that you cost people

00:18:51.200 --> 00:18:52.710
their houses and everything.'No, they

00:18:52.720 --> 00:18:55.430
sold their houses

00:18:55.440 --> 00:18:57.510
to downsize because they thought

00:18:57.520 --> 00:18:59.510
the economy was going to crash. I didn't

00:18:59.520 --> 00:19:01.590
cause anybody to lose their house; it

00:19:01.590 --> 00:19:01.600
wasn't

00:19:01.600 --> 00:19:03.190
because of anything I said. They

00:19:03.200 --> 00:19:03.990
were already

00:19:05.360 --> 00:19:06.390
preppers

00:19:06.390 --> 00:19:06.400
and

00:19:06.400 --> 00:19:08.710
were downsizing

00:19:08.720 --> 00:19:09.830
their homes. Now, people try to say,

00:19:09.840 --> 00:19:11.190
'Well, Brandon, you cost them their

00:19:11.190 --> 00:19:11.200
house.'I

00:19:11.200 --> 00:19:13.029
saw YouTube videos and I said, 'Are

00:19:13.039 --> 00:19:14.549
you kidding? I never cost anybody their

00:19:14.549 --> 00:19:14.559
house.'They

00:19:14.559 --> 00:19:16.630
sold their

00:19:16.630 --> 00:19:16.640
houses

00:19:16.640 --> 00:19:17.990
because of things that we were talking

00:19:18.000 --> 00:19:19.270
about and praying over.

00:19:20.080 --> 00:19:21.909
We were all in a prayer group; it's

00:19:21.919 --> 00:19:23.750
a church thing. It isn't on

00:19:24.240 --> 00:19:26.230
me. Adults are adults.

00:19:26.240 --> 00:19:28.070
If you're an adult, you put your big boy or

00:19:28.070 --> 00:19:28.080
big girl

00:19:28.080 --> 00:19:29.990
pants on; I'm not responsible

00:19:30.000 --> 00:19:33.270
for your household. But we pray. Now, if

00:19:33.280 --> 00:19:34.710
you're not a part of it, you automatically

00:19:34.720 --> 00:19:36.070
want to see... like the other pastors, they

00:19:36.080 --> 00:19:37.270
don't like some of the stuff you're

00:19:37.280 --> 00:19:39.430
saying because they're

00:19:39.430 --> 00:19:39.440
seeker-friendly.

00:19:39.440 --> 00:19:41.590
99% of the seeker-friendlies don't

00:19:41.600 --> 00:19:43.590
want to talk about this stuff,

00:19:43.600 --> 00:19:44.950
and they go, 'Well, you're causing

00:19:44.950 --> 00:19:44.960
fear.'So,

00:19:44.960 --> 00:19:46.710
shut up. We don't want

00:19:46.720 --> 00:19:48.630
you talking in our church anymore.

00:19:48.640 --> 00:19:51.270
That's fine. I have an opinion and I'm

00:19:51.280 --> 00:19:52.549
entitled to it, but I'm not telling you

00:19:52.559 --> 00:19:53.909
to do anything.

00:19:53.919 --> 00:19:54.789
This is what we do,

00:19:55.600 --> 00:19:57.190
and people have

00:19:57.200 --> 00:19:58.789
asked. The other part

00:19:58.799 --> 00:20:01.510
was coins.

00:20:01.520 --> 00:20:06.070
I like old silver coins

00:20:06.080 --> 00:20:08.230
that are tradable.

00:20:08.240 --> 00:20:09.990
Having things like this—this is a

00:20:10.000 --> 00:20:11.990
silver coin, an old coin

00:20:15.919 --> 00:20:17.830
from

00:20:19.679 --> 00:20:20.950
1812.

00:20:22.640 --> 00:20:25.029
Old coins like that are

00:20:25.039 --> 00:20:26.870
junk silver.

00:20:26.880 --> 00:20:29.350
I

00:20:29.360 --> 00:20:30.870
always try to think outside the box

00:20:30.870 --> 00:20:30.880
regarding

00:20:30.880 --> 00:20:33.590
bartering. Well, if you have a chicken

00:20:33.600 --> 00:20:36.070
and I have a piece of silver,

00:20:36.080 --> 00:20:38.549
could I take this and barter with you to

00:20:38.559 --> 00:20:41.270
get a chicken? Because I like chicken. And

00:20:41.280 --> 00:20:43.510
you can make a pot of noodles with this

00:20:43.520 --> 00:20:46.070
wheat. You make noodles out of

00:20:46.080 --> 00:20:47.830
it, boil a chicken, and you have chicken

00:20:47.840 --> 00:20:49.430
noodle soup.

00:20:49.440 --> 00:20:53.990
It's all part of

00:20:53.990 --> 00:20:54.000
it.

00:20:54.000 --> 00:20:57.110
And if you have change—I've found a lot of spare change

00:20:59.120 --> 00:21:02.310
in the past that would have old coins,

00:21:02.320 --> 00:21:04.390
like quarters

00:21:04.390 --> 00:21:04.400
from

00:21:04.400 --> 00:21:07.029
1964 and older. If you go on YouTube and

00:21:07.039 --> 00:21:10.070
search it, you'll see they're worth more than a

00:21:10.080 --> 00:21:11.830
quarter; they're worth

00:21:11.840 --> 00:21:14.310
a few dollars

00:21:14.310 --> 00:21:14.320
because

00:21:14.320 --> 00:21:17.190
they're still 90%

00:21:17.200 --> 00:21:17.750
silver.

00:21:18.320 --> 00:21:20.950
So, having junk

00:21:20.960 --> 00:21:22.789
silver for bartering

00:21:22.799 --> 00:21:23.590
and trading

00:21:23.590 --> 00:21:23.600
is

00:21:23.600 --> 00:21:23.909
good.

00:21:23.919 --> 00:21:26.230
The other part is firearms.

00:21:26.240 --> 00:21:30.549
I know it's controversial

00:21:30.549 --> 00:21:30.559
and

00:21:30.559 --> 00:21:32.950
people get upset with me,

00:21:32.960 --> 00:21:35.669
but I am a man who believes in the

00:21:35.679 --> 00:21:39.190
Second Amendment. I believe that we have

00:21:39.200 --> 00:21:41.029
the right to bear arms

00:21:41.029 --> 00:21:41.039
and

00:21:41.039 --> 00:21:43.830
the right to defend your family. I

00:21:43.840 --> 00:21:45.990
do not back away from it or shy

00:21:46.000 --> 00:21:47.590
away from it. I know there's a lot of

00:21:47.600 --> 00:21:49.590
Christians that get really upset at me

00:21:49.600 --> 00:21:52.630
about that, but my wife and I are very

00:21:52.640 --> 00:21:55.270
trained in protecting ourselves with our

00:21:55.280 --> 00:21:57.990
firearms. You come through my front door

00:21:58.000 --> 00:22:00.230
uninvited and you kick it in, you won't

00:22:00.240 --> 00:22:02.870
be here the next day. I'm just telling

00:22:02.880 --> 00:22:05.669
you where we are. Now, people don't like

00:22:05.679 --> 00:22:07.510
that, but that's the

00:22:07.510 --> 00:22:07.520
honest-to-God

00:22:07.520 --> 00:22:09.590
truth. You kick in my door, you're not

00:22:09.600 --> 00:22:10.789
going to be here. You come in and

00:22:10.799 --> 00:22:12.630
try to hurt me, you're going to go home

00:22:12.640 --> 00:22:14.789
early. I'll pray for you as you're

00:22:14.799 --> 00:22:17.430
dying, but you're going home.

00:22:17.440 --> 00:22:19.110
That's just the way it is. People don't

00:22:19.120 --> 00:22:20.630
like that, but that's just where

00:22:20.630 --> 00:22:20.640
Diana

00:22:20.640 --> 00:22:23.270
and I are. If that comes across to

00:22:23.280 --> 00:22:25.190
you like, 'Brandon, I can't believe you'd say

00:22:25.190 --> 00:22:25.200
that,'then

00:22:25.200 --> 00:22:27.270
this channel is

00:22:27.280 --> 00:22:29.669
not for you. We're just trying to help

00:22:29.679 --> 00:22:30.310
you.

00:22:30.799 --> 00:22:31.990
That's the way we were raised; that's

00:22:32.000 --> 00:22:32.549
southern.

00:22:34.559 --> 00:22:36.549
Even as a kid, we

00:22:36.549 --> 00:22:36.559
believed

00:22:36.559 --> 00:22:38.950
in shotguns, rifles, and

00:22:38.960 --> 00:22:41.830
AR-15s.

00:22:41.840 --> 00:22:43.590
I train my kids on how to shoot

00:22:43.600 --> 00:22:46.710
them. I

00:22:46.720 --> 00:22:49.510
know where we are in the last days.

00:22:49.520 --> 00:22:52.310
I believe in praying for you and I

00:22:52.320 --> 00:22:54.710
believe in raising the dead,

00:22:54.720 --> 00:22:56.549
but if you touch my family,

00:22:56.559 --> 00:22:58.230
it's another

00:22:58.240 --> 00:22:59.750
story.

